\section{Comparison with Observations}

The ringdown signal observed in GW150914 \cite{LIGO2016} corresponds to frequencies of order
\begin{equation}
M\omega \sim 0.37 - 0.09i.
\end{equation}

Within this model, deviations appear near the critical regime while remaining consistent at leading order.

%--------------------------------------------------

\section{Conclusion}

We identified a critical parameter
\begin{equation}
\beta_c = \left(\frac{4}{27}\right)^{1/3}
\end{equation}
governing horizon formation.

The model predicts coupled geometric and spectral transitions with potential observational signatures.

